        public boolean isProactiveSupportEnabled()
        A check on whether Proactive Support (PS) is enabled or not. PS is disabled when CONFLUENT_SUPPORT_METRICS_ENABLE_CONFIG is false or is not defined
        Returns:
        false if PS is not enabled, true if PS is enabled

      • isCaseSensitiveCustomerId

        public static boolean isCaseSensitiveCustomerId(java.lang.String customerId)
        The 15-character alpha-numeric customer IDs are case-sensitive, others are case-insensitive. The old-style customer ID "c\\d{1,30}" maybe look the same as a 15-character alpha-numeric ID, if its length is also 15 characters. In that case, this method will return true.
        Parameters:
        customerId - The value of "confluent.support.customer.id".
        Returns:
        true if customer Id is case sensitive
